I'm implementing a shortcut, but the `isKeyPressed` function in RawKeyboardListener behaves differently depending on the language of the user's keyboard. I don't know if this is a bug or not, but I want to create a shortcut that behaves the same regardless of the user's language.

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Execute `flutter run` on the code sample.
2. Connect the Bluetooth keyboard to your iOS or iPad.
3. When entering `E` or `e` in English, it works as `is KeyE pressed = true`.
4. When entering the Korean `ㄷ` corresponding to `E` on the English keyboard, it works as `is KeyE pressed = false`.

**Expected results:**
I would like to receive the same `event.isKeyPressed(LogicalKeyboardKey.keyE)` result as `true` whether I type `ㄷ` on a Korean keyboard or an English keyboard when I type `E`.

The physicalKeyboardKey recognizes the Korean word `ㄷ` as Key E. However, the `isKeyPressed` function returns `false` because it checks whether they are the same using LogicalKeyboardKey internally.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26322627/172360844-059490ef-2bd7-42f0-aefd-c7c6ca74b4e3.MP4

<details>
<summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/services.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatefulWidget {
  const MyApp({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  State<MyApp> createState() => _MyAppState();
}

class _MyAppState extends State<MyApp> {
  FocusNode focusNode = FocusNode();
  bool isKeyEPressed = false;
  Set<PhysicalKeyboardKey> pressedKeys = {};
  RawKeyEvent? keyEvent;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        body: RawKeyboardListener(
          focusNode: focusNode,
          onKey: (event) {
            if (event.runtimeType == RawKeyDownEvent) {
              setState(() {
                keyEvent = event;
                pressedKeys = RawKeyboard.instance.physicalKeysPressed;
                isKeyEPressed = event.isKeyPressed(LogicalKeyboardKey.keyE);
              });
            }
          },
          child: SizedBox(
            width: double.infinity,
            child: Padding(
              padding: const EdgeInsets.all(8.0),
              child: Column(
                mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
                children: [
                  const Text("English keyboard E == Korean keyboard ㄷ"),
                  const SizedBox(height: 16),

                  /// TextField
                  const Text("<TextField>"),
                  const TextField(autofocus: true),
                  const SizedBox(height: 16),

                  /// Pressed Keys
                  const Text("<pressedKeys>"),
                  Text(pressedKeys.toString(), textAlign: TextAlign.center),

                  /// Key event
                  const SizedBox(height: 16),
                  const Text("<keyEvent>"),
                  Text(keyEvent.toString(), textAlign: TextAlign.center),

                  /// Is KeyE Pressed
                  const SizedBox(height: 16),
                  const Text("<is keyE pressed>"),
                  Text(isKeyEPressed.toString()),
                ],
              ),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
